name: Anneke Grönloh
description: '''Johanna Louise''' "'''Anneke'''" '''Grönloh''' ({{IPA|nl|ˈɑnəkə ˈɡrʏnloː}}; 7 June 1942 – 14 September 2018) was a Dutch singer. She had a successful career starting in 1959 that lasted throughout the 1960s, and scored a hit with "[[Brandend Zand]]", one of the best-selling Dutch songs of all time.
